"{\"description\":\"Team Leader (Welding & Grinding) x 2 at Hither Green, GB. Responsible for directing and inspiring a team involved in inspection, faulting, maintenance, and renewal. The role involves establishing safety arrangements, ensuring the highest standards, and compiling essential reports. Essential criteria include experience in organizing and controlling work delivery, excellent communication skills, knowledge of maintenance techniques and relevant standards, and being a clear and inspirational leader. Desirable criteria include holding or working towards an NVQ level 2 or 3, willingness to drive vehicles, and holding safety critical competencies. The role involves days, nights, and weekend working, and is subject to drug and alcohol testing and a competency-based interview process.\",\"howToApply\":\"To apply for this role, click 'apply now' and complete the form. The salary for this role is \\nï¿½40639. The closing date for applications is 17th November 2023. Late applications will not be accepted. All offers of employment are conditional upon satisfactory completion of pre-employment checks, including a drugs and alcohol test. See the job description for detailed information on the recruitment process and the importance of safety in the railway environment.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Experience of organising and controlling the safe and efficient delivery of work\",\"Excellent communication skills, both in person and in writing\",\"Knowledge of discipline-specific maintenance, inspection, faulting and renewal techniques\",\"Knowledge of relevant standards, procedures and instructions\",\"A clear and inspirational leader with a strong sense of direction\",\"Hold Safety Critical Competencies COSS CRP and PC\",\"Hold Tr04 and Tr11 Competence\"],\"desirable\":[\"Hold or be working towards an NVQ level 2 or 3 (or equivalent) in a relevant subject or have attained the appropriate level of knowledge gained through equivalent relevant experience\",\"Able and willing to drive vehicles as required by business need, this may also include driving vehicles up to 7.5t and a requirement to upgrade their driving licence by undertaking additional training\",\"Hold Safety Critical Competencies Strapping, NSCD (Ops) and Engineering Supervisor\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Establish safety arrangements and ensure the highest standards are maintained\",\"Organize, control, and motivate a high performing team involved in inspection, faulting, maintenance, and renewal\",\"Proactively control and check the quality of work and the competence of the team\",\"Compile a range of vital reports\",\"Direct, organise and motivate a high performing team\",\"Work flexibly, including days, nights, and weekend shifts\",\"Undergo drug and alcohol testing, and pass a competency-based interview process\"]}}"